Text.SourceString: Here, I made you some breakfast, honey. It's a <NPCName>Zarah</>'s special!//Don't knock it till you've tried it.
Text.LocalizedString: Here, I made you some breakfast, honey. It's a <NPCName>Zarah</>'s special!//Don't knock it till you've tried it.

Text.SourceString: I made you something, honey. Figured you could use a hearty meal!
Text.LocalizedString: I made you something, honey. Figured you could use a hearty meal!

Text.SourceString: The sunrise was spectacular today, honey. There's something about the first light of day that makes even the biggest problems seem small.
Text.LocalizedString: The sunrise was spectacular today, honey. There's something about the first light of day that makes even the biggest problems seem small.

Text.SourceString: Those forest mosquitoes are pesky little buggers.//No matter how much repellent you use, they always find a way.
Text.LocalizedString: Those forest mosquitoes are pesky little buggers.//No matter how much repellent you use, they always find a way.

Text.SourceString: Being here, on our farm...has shown me a different kind of adventure.//A quieter, slower one. It's...nice.
Text.LocalizedString: Being here, on our farm...has shown me a different kind of adventure.//A quieter, slower one. It's...nice.

Text.SourceString: Have you noticed how the wind changes direction before a storm hits, hun? It's like the island is telling us to brace ourselves.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you noticed how the wind changes direction before a storm hits, hun? It's like the island is telling us to brace ourselves.

Text.SourceString: Are these roosters crowing at dawn ours or are they <NpcName>Jack</>'s, hun?
Text.LocalizedString: Are these roosters crowing at dawn ours or are they <NpcName>Jack</>'s, hun?

Text.SourceString: Cooking on solid ground is much easier than on a rocking boat, hands down.
Text.LocalizedString: Cooking on solid ground is much easier than on a rocking boat, hands down.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I should try cooking some of the traditional seafarer's meals. It could be interesting to bring a bit of the sea to our table.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I should try cooking some of the traditional seafarer's meals. It could be interesting to bring a bit of the sea to our table.

Text.SourceString: Not feeling up to a town visit today, but I should probably check in on my boat.//Crack open some windows...let the stale air out.
Text.LocalizedString: Not feeling up to a town visit today, but I should probably check in on my boat.//Crack open some windows...let the stale air out.

Text.SourceString: Do you think we should grab some of <NpcName>Sam</>'s cookies, honey?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think we should grab some of <NpcName>Sam</>'s cookies, honey?

Text.SourceString: I was all set to get some flour for us, but it's raining outside. Well, there's always tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I was all set to get some flour for us, but it's raining outside. Well, there's always tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I'll fish later.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I'll fish later.

Text.SourceString: Do we really need to 'do' anything today? Can't we redefine productivity to mean 'staying in bed and cuddling all day'?
Text.LocalizedString: Do we really need to 'do' anything today? Can't we redefine productivity to mean 'staying in bed and cuddling all day'?

Text.SourceString: I'm officially declaring today a do-nothing day. What's stopping us from staying in bed and cuddling all day?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm officially declaring today a do-nothing day. What's stopping us from staying in bed and cuddling all day?

Text.SourceString: There's something calming about just sitting by the water, waiting for a bite. It's like meditation, but with more seafood.
Text.LocalizedString: There's something calming about just sitting by the water, waiting for a bite. It's like meditation, but with more seafood.

Text.SourceString: If I were a bird, I'd probably be a seagull. They've got the right idea, living life by the sea.
Text.LocalizedString: If I were a bird, I'd probably be a seagull. They've got the right idea, living life by the sea.

Text.SourceString: Honey, you've got this knack for making even the simplest things feel like an adventure, and I love it.
Text.LocalizedString: Honey, you've got this knack for making even the simplest things feel like an adventure, and I love it.

Text.SourceString: Gimme a kiss, hun...come closer.
Text.LocalizedString: Gimme a kiss, hun...come closer.

Text.SourceString: Wow, you're really turning up the heat today, aren't you? I love what you're wearing.
Text.LocalizedString: Wow, you're really turning up the heat today, aren't you? I love what you're wearing.

Text.SourceString: You make the best-grilled fish, hun...no, seriously.
Text.LocalizedString: You make the best-grilled fish, hun...no, seriously.

Text.SourceString: I've been eating like some sort of health guru since we moved here, hun. I can feel my body thanking me.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been eating like some sort of health guru since we moved here, hun. I can feel my body thanking me.

Text.SourceString: Can you hear that? That's the sweet symphony of <NpcName>Jack</>'s animals. I swear they're closer to us than we are to each other.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you hear that? That's the sweet symphony of <NpcName>Jack</>'s animals. I swear they're closer to us than we are to each other.

Text.SourceString: Just kidding, honey, nothing is closer than we are, haha!
Text.LocalizedString: Just kidding, honey, nothing is closer than we are, haha!

Text.SourceString: Feels like we're living on the edge of the world, doesn't it? Makes the trek to town feel like a mini-adventure.//<portrait=happy>It's a good thing it keeps the guests at bay.
Text.LocalizedString: Feels like we're living on the edge of the world, doesn't it? Makes the trek to town feel like a mini-adventure.//<portrait=happy>It's a good thing it keeps the guests at bay.

Text.SourceString: How did the world treat my favorite farmer today, hun?
Text.LocalizedString: How did the world treat my favorite farmer today, hun?

Text.SourceString: How's your day, honey? Tell me all about it!
Text.LocalizedString: How's your day, honey? Tell me all about it!

Text.SourceString: I've changed the bedsheets today. Prepare for a night of slumber so divine, you'd think we're sleeping on clouds.
Text.LocalizedString: I've changed the bedsheets today. Prepare for a night of slumber so divine, you'd think we're sleeping on clouds.

Text.SourceString: I'm in the mood for some TV. How about you?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm in the mood for some TV. How about you?

Text.SourceString: How's the life of my favorite farmer today, hun?
Text.LocalizedString: How's the life of my favorite farmer today, hun?

Text.SourceString: It's getting a bit cold out, let's head to the hot spring next week, hun.
Text.LocalizedString: It's getting a bit cold out, let's head to the hot spring next week, hun.

Text.SourceString: Camping in a cavern for more than two days is a nasty business. I don’t miss it.//<portrait=annoyed>How can a place be damp and hot at the same time?
Text.LocalizedString: Camping in a cavern for more than two days is a nasty business. I don’t miss it.//<portrait=annoyed>How can a place be damp and hot at the same time?

Text.SourceString: Life feels bland when I’m not after something…//<portrait=annoyed>It's a pity, really. I feel stuck, you know? Like I'm trapped in an endless cycle of one adventure after another.
Text.LocalizedString: Life feels bland when I’m not after something…//<portrait=annoyed>It's a pity, really. I feel stuck, you know? Like I'm trapped in an endless cycle of one adventure after another.

Text.SourceString: Now, is that a good thing or a bad thing? I’ll let you decide.
Text.LocalizedString: Now, is that a good thing or a bad thing? I’ll let you decide.

Text.SourceString: You know, I've always had this itch to garden.//Now that we're here, it's like the universe gave me a green thumb and a plot of soil.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, I've always had this itch to garden.//Now that we're here, it's like the universe gave me a green thumb and a plot of soil.

Text.SourceString: Pro tip, <PlayerName>$player</>. Always keep a trusty weapon in your bag, just in case you come across any pesky critters on your journey. You never know!
Text.LocalizedString: Pro tip, <PlayerName>$player</>. Always keep a trusty weapon in your bag, just in case you come across any pesky critters on your journey. You never know!

Text.SourceString: You know what I feel? We're all players in this grand game of life, destined for endless adventures... Yeah...
Text.LocalizedString: You know what I feel? We're all players in this grand game of life, destined for endless adventures... Yeah...

Text.SourceString: Wow! That would be the dream!
Text.LocalizedString: Wow! That would be the dream!

Text.SourceString: I've had my fair share of camping and roasted chestnuts.//It’s safe to say I’m a bit sick of them now. Yuck.
Text.LocalizedString: I've had my fair share of camping and roasted chestnuts.//It’s safe to say I’m a bit sick of them now. Yuck.

Text.SourceString: I used to have a bad allergy to cats.//<portrait=normal>But thankfully, I outgrew it.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to have a bad allergy to cats.//<portrait=normal>But thankfully, I outgrew it.

Text.SourceString: I can play with cats now, but I still sneeze here and there… It’s not bad at all, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I can play with cats now, but I still sneeze here and there… It’s not bad at all, though.

Text.SourceString: There are plenty of treasure chests in the sea or buried in the cavern.//If you break them open, there may be valuable things in them.
Text.LocalizedString: There are plenty of treasure chests in the sea or buried in the cavern.//If you break them open, there may be valuable things in them.

Text.SourceString: A little tip from one treasure hunter to another: Keep your eyes peeled for those chests and give 'em a good whack.
Text.LocalizedString: A little tip from one treasure hunter to another: Keep your eyes peeled for those chests and give 'em a good whack.

Text.SourceString: Peanut and Butter are smart cats. I always see them around town, jumping up and down.
Text.LocalizedString: Peanut and Butter are smart cats. I always see them around town, jumping up and down.

Text.SourceString: Quick little furballs, aren't they?
Text.LocalizedString: Quick little furballs, aren't they?

Text.SourceString: I once got into trouble with a client because he wanted his money back. The problem was the government took the treasure I found, and my client sued me for unfinished work.
Text.LocalizedString: I once got into trouble with a client because he wanted his money back. The problem was the government took the treasure I found, and my client sued me for unfinished work.

Text.SourceString: It was a mess. My hands were tied, and I couldn’t do anything about it. Good thing it’s all behind me.
Text.LocalizedString: It was a mess. My hands were tied, and I couldn’t do anything about it. Good thing it’s all behind me.

Text.SourceString: Now that Spring is here, I’m ready to search for treasure again.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that Spring is here, I’m ready to search for treasure again.

Text.SourceString: If you ask me, Spring and Fall are the prime seasons for seeking hidden treasures.//It's not too scorching hot, and the daylight hours are just right.
Text.LocalizedString: If you ask me, Spring and Fall are the prime seasons for seeking hidden treasures.//It's not too scorching hot, and the daylight hours are just right.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait for the Cherry Blossom Festival. There’s going to be a lot of good food.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait for the Cherry Blossom Festival. There’s going to be a lot of good food.

Text.SourceString: Are you ready for the start of a new year, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I’m raring to go.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you ready for the start of a new year, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I’m raring to go.

Text.SourceString: The mud can be annoying in Spring, but it’s still better than the bone-chilling Winter for treasure hunting.
Text.LocalizedString: The mud can be annoying in Spring, but it’s still better than the bone-chilling Winter for treasure hunting.

Text.SourceString: What are we bringing for the hot pot tomorrow, <PlayerName>$player</>? We should bring cookies.
Text.LocalizedString: What are we bringing for the hot pot tomorrow, <PlayerName>$player</>? We should bring cookies.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice that the sun is up longer, but… Never mind.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice that the sun is up longer, but… Never mind.

Text.SourceString: You never realize how important daylight is until you find yourself scrounging around the woods in the dark, looking for valuables, and end up bringing home a bunch of useless things.//Trash, pretty much… Yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: You never realize how important daylight is until you find yourself scrounging around the woods in the dark, looking for valuables, and end up bringing home a bunch of useless things.//Trash, pretty much… Yeah.

Text.SourceString: Why on earth wouldn't we laze around the beach the entire Summer? Sounds like a perfect plan to me!
Text.LocalizedString: Why on earth wouldn't we laze around the beach the entire Summer? Sounds like a perfect plan to me!

Text.SourceString: I get it, the Beach Cleanup Festival is important, but do they really have to make it an all-day affair?//<portrait=normal>Just a thought, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I get it, the Beach Cleanup Festival is important, but do they really have to make it an all-day affair?//<portrait=normal>Just a thought, you know?

Text.SourceString: It’s pretty much Fall, and… Wait, no it isn’t.//<portrait=thinking>It’s only the second week of Summer… I thought it was the 20th already.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s pretty much Fall, and… Wait, no it isn’t.//<portrait=thinking>It’s only the second week of Summer… I thought it was the 20th already.

Text.SourceString: Lately, I've been reeling in quite a haul of groupers.//<portrait=normal>They may not win any beauty contests, that's for sure. But once you grill 'em up, all fish taste pretty much the same.
Text.LocalizedString: Lately, I've been reeling in quite a haul of groupers.//<portrait=normal>They may not win any beauty contests, that's for sure. But once you grill 'em up, all fish taste pretty much the same.

Text.SourceString: I’m not saying you can only eat grilled fish in Fall. Grilled fish is top-tier food that can be enjoyed any time of day, any time of year.//<portrait=happy>But it’s so much better when the weather’s a bit frisky. Like in Fall.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not saying you can only eat grilled fish in Fall. Grilled fish is top-tier food that can be enjoyed any time of day, any time of year.//<portrait=happy>But it’s so much better when the weather’s a bit frisky. Like in Fall.

Text.SourceString: You wouldn't believe it, but I stumble upon crabs on our farm every now and then.//<portrait=thinking>I think it's that rice field up top. Swear it's a crab carnival up there!
Text.LocalizedString: You wouldn't believe it, but I stumble upon crabs on our farm every now and then.//<portrait=thinking>I think it's that rice field up top. Swear it's a crab carnival up there!

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to <NPCName>Betty’s</> mooncakes. It’s a shame she doesn’t make them more often.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to <NPCName>Betty’s</> mooncakes. It’s a shame she doesn’t make them more often.

Text.SourceString: Daylight is getting shorter and shorter. Looks like I’ll have to stop my exploration pretty soon.
Text.LocalizedString: Daylight is getting shorter and shorter. Looks like I’ll have to stop my exploration pretty soon.

Text.SourceString: It’s not just the cold that makes treasure hunting a pain in Winter. Soil is much harder to dig too… Pretty much concrete at this point.//Better to just wait until the ice melts.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not just the cold that makes treasure hunting a pain in Winter. Soil is much harder to dig too… Pretty much concrete at this point.//Better to just wait until the ice melts.

Text.SourceString: The boat isn't really the best place to live in Winter. There's a lot of wind, and it's really hard to keep the heat going.//I'm glad we don't live there, hun.
Text.LocalizedString: The boat isn't really the best place to live in Winter. There's a lot of wind, and it's really hard to keep the heat going.//I'm glad we don't live there, hun.

Text.SourceString: It’s going to be one hot Summer, isn’t it?//I can already tell.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s going to be one hot Summer, isn’t it?//I can already tell.

Text.SourceString: I went on an adventure to discover a buried temple one time and filled my bag with weapons and no food.//<portrait=normal>I thought there’d be food for me wherever I went. Being not picky and all.
Text.LocalizedString: I went on an adventure to discover a buried temple one time and filled my bag with weapons and no food.//<portrait=normal>I thought there’d be food for me wherever I went. Being not picky and all.

Text.SourceString: I could <Italic>not</> have been more wrong. There was hardly any food, and I ran out of energy in the middle of a battle.//<portrait=annoyed>I passed out and was found by a local blacksmith.
Text.LocalizedString: I could <Italic>not</> have been more wrong. There was hardly any food, and I ran out of energy in the middle of a battle.//<portrait=annoyed>I passed out and was found by a local blacksmith.

Text.SourceString: I learn something new every day on this island if I look closely enough.
Text.LocalizedString: I learn something new every day on this island if I look closely enough.

Text.SourceString: I hate roasted nuts. Nuts are easy to find and simple to roast, but they taste like rotten charcoal.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate roasted nuts. Nuts are easy to find and simple to roast, but they taste like rotten charcoal.

Text.SourceString: I gathered several coconuts around the inn the other day, and I haven’t touched them.//<portrait=thinking>What should I make with them? Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: I gathered several coconuts around the inn the other day, and I haven’t touched them.//<portrait=thinking>What should I make with them? Hmm…

Text.SourceString: The only thing I know how to make with coconut milk is lodeh.//<portrait=normal>But I’m not in the mood for it. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: The only thing I know how to make with coconut milk is lodeh.//<portrait=normal>But I’m not in the mood for it. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: You can tell it’s Fall from all these chestnuts. They’re everywhere, like weeds!
Text.LocalizedString: You can tell it’s Fall from all these chestnuts. They’re everywhere, like weeds!

Text.SourceString: Oh! Do you feel that wind?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! Do you feel that wind?

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to get any warm sunlight lately. It’s making me feel a bit down.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to get any warm sunlight lately. It’s making me feel a bit down.

Text.SourceString: You’re always welcome here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re always welcome here, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: The weather couldn’t be better for reading… Or swimming.//<portrait=surprised>Or heck, fishing!
Text.LocalizedString: The weather couldn’t be better for reading… Or swimming.//<portrait=surprised>Or heck, fishing!

Text.SourceString: I caught some fish a little while ago.//<portrait=thinking>I think I’ll make soup with them for dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: I caught some fish a little while ago.//<portrait=thinking>I think I’ll make soup with them for dinner.

Text.SourceString: Well, I personally prefer grilled fish to fish soup.//But today, it just feels like soup kind of weather.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I personally prefer grilled fish to fish soup.//But today, it just feels like soup kind of weather.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll head inside in a little bit and make myself a warm meal.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll head inside in a little bit and make myself a warm meal.

Text.SourceString: Oh! Do you feel that?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! Do you feel that?

Text.SourceString: The wind is getting intense.
Text.LocalizedString: The wind is getting intense.

Text.SourceString: The weather couldn’t be better for reading… Or swimming.//<portrait=surprised>Or heck, fishing!
Text.LocalizedString: The weather couldn’t be better for reading… Or swimming.//<portrait=surprised>Or heck, fishing!

Text.SourceString: I caught some fish a little while ago.//<portrait=thinking>I think I’ll make soup with them for dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: I caught some fish a little while ago.//<portrait=thinking>I think I’ll make soup with them for dinner.

Text.SourceString: Well, I personally prefer grilled fish to fish soup.//But today, it just feels like soup kind of weather.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I personally prefer grilled fish to fish soup.//But today, it just feels like soup kind of weather.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll head inside in a little bit and make myself a warm meal.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll head inside in a little bit and make myself a warm meal.

Text.SourceString: Oh! Do you feel that?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! Do you feel that?

Text.SourceString: Well, I personally prefer grilled fish to fish soup.//But today, it just feels like soup kind of weather.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I personally prefer grilled fish to fish soup.//But today, it just feels like soup kind of weather.

Text.SourceString: You have a lot of snow on you, hun.
Text.LocalizedString: You have a lot of snow on you, hun.

Text.SourceString: There’s something about this forest that feels mysterious to me.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something about this forest that feels mysterious to me.

Text.SourceString: Should I move my boat here?
Text.LocalizedString: Should I move my boat here?

Text.SourceString: It's closer to home, don't you think?
Text.LocalizedString: It's closer to home, don't you think?

Text.SourceString: The weather is great for a beach day today.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather is great for a beach day today.

Text.SourceString: I’m supposed to go to the forest today, yet here we are.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m supposed to go to the forest today, yet here we are.

Text.SourceString: Please excuse the mess around here. It may seem chaotic, but trust me, I have a system in place.
Text.LocalizedString: Please excuse the mess around here. It may seem chaotic, but trust me, I have a system in place.

Text.SourceString: I need to keep things where they are, or else I'll never be able to find my belongings. So, mind your step, please.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want you to accidentally step on my things.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to keep things where they are, or else I'll never be able to find my belongings. So, mind your step, please.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want you to accidentally step on my things.

Text.SourceString: It feels good to be back here, hun.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels good to be back here, hun.

Text.SourceString: I'll tidy up a bit around here before making my way home.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll tidy up a bit around here before making my way home.

Text.SourceString: The breeze feels different on land compared to out at sea.//<portrait=happy>Out there, it feels like it goes on forever!
Text.LocalizedString: The breeze feels different on land compared to out at sea.//<portrait=happy>Out there, it feels like it goes on forever!

Text.SourceString: If you stumble upon something on the island that looks super old, make sure to take it to the museum! It could be a real rare artifact.
Text.LocalizedString: If you stumble upon something on the island that looks super old, make sure to take it to the museum! It could be a real rare artifact.

Text.SourceString: I often wonder about the civilizations that were here before us.//What was happening hundreds of years ago on this very spot?
Text.LocalizedString: I often wonder about the civilizations that were here before us.//What was happening hundreds of years ago on this very spot?

Text.SourceString: Life moves more slowly out here. It’s nice not to have to stick to a work schedule, isn’t it?//That's just how I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: Life moves more slowly out here. It’s nice not to have to stick to a work schedule, isn’t it?//That's just how I like it.

Text.SourceString: On the flip side, having a schedule can bring some structure to life.//I guess there are good things and bad things about it.
Text.LocalizedString: On the flip side, having a schedule can bring some structure to life.//I guess there are good things and bad things about it.

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Achoo!</>
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Achoo!</>

Text.SourceString: Excuse me! I’m so sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>.//My nose is acting up.
Text.LocalizedString: Excuse me! I’m so sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>.//My nose is acting up.

Text.SourceString: There’s tons of fish around here, you know. I see them under the surface all the time.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s tons of fish around here, you know. I see them under the surface all the time.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if there are shipwrecks down there… I bet there’s treasure!
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if there are shipwrecks down there… I bet there’s treasure!

Text.SourceString: Sometimes people ask if my boat has a name.//I’ve never really thought about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes people ask if my boat has a name.//I’ve never really thought about it.

Text.SourceString: I've always considered it simply "mine" and never felt the need for anything more. But now, it feels more like "ours."
Text.LocalizedString: I've always considered it simply "mine" and never felt the need for anything more. But now, it feels more like "ours."

Text.SourceString: Even though the air feels warmer now, the ocean still has a chilly bite to it. So, I'll hold off on diving off the deck of my boat for now.//<portrait=happy>Wouldn't wanna turn into a popsicle, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: Even though the air feels warmer now, the ocean still has a chilly bite to it. So, I'll hold off on diving off the deck of my boat for now.//<portrait=happy>Wouldn't wanna turn into a popsicle, you know?

Text.SourceString: Coral Island is always beautiful this time of year.//<portrait=normal>It’s beautiful year-round, but it really blooms in the Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: Coral Island is always beautiful this time of year.//<portrait=normal>It’s beautiful year-round, but it really blooms in the Spring.

Text.SourceString: The Summer haze makes adventuring much more enjoyable. Everything feels heavy, still, and mysterious.
Text.LocalizedString: The Summer haze makes adventuring much more enjoyable. Everything feels heavy, still, and mysterious.

Text.SourceString: Do you think we’ll get any storms soon, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’d rather know ahead of time if they’re coming.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think we’ll get any storms soon, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’d rather know ahead of time if they’re coming.

Text.SourceString: If a storm’s coming, I have to prep the boat… It’s a long process.
Text.LocalizedString: If a storm’s coming, I have to prep the boat… It’s a long process.

Text.SourceString: Having a Summer birthday isn’t too bad. It means I get extra hours of daylight to celebrate.
Text.LocalizedString: Having a Summer birthday isn’t too bad. It means I get extra hours of daylight to celebrate.

Text.SourceString: Not that I do much celebrating, though.//That’s not really my style.
Text.LocalizedString: Not that I do much celebrating, though.//That’s not really my style.

Text.SourceString: Feel that slight chill in the air? Winter's creeping closer, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//Time to bundle up and brace ourselves for some chilly days ahead.
Text.LocalizedString: Feel that slight chill in the air? Winter's creeping closer, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//Time to bundle up and brace ourselves for some chilly days ahead.

Text.SourceString: I feel closest to nature in Fall. The beautiful colors, piles of leaves on the ground… It’s something to be thankful for.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel closest to nature in Fall. The beautiful colors, piles of leaves on the ground… It’s something to be thankful for.

Text.SourceString: As much as I love my boat, I used to feel a little trapped during Winter.//I didn't want to stay inside, but I didn't want to go out into the cold air, either.
Text.LocalizedString: As much as I love my boat, I used to feel a little trapped during Winter.//I didn't want to stay inside, but I didn't want to go out into the cold air, either.

Text.SourceString: I'm not afraid to get down and dirty. Grime, dust, you name it—I've embraced it all.//But you know what I despise? Getting wet. Ugh, it's the worst!
Text.LocalizedString: I'm not afraid to get down and dirty. Grime, dust, you name it—I've embraced it all.//But you know what I despise? Getting wet. Ugh, it's the worst!

Text.SourceString: Look at it pour out there. Do you think it’ll clear up soon?
Text.LocalizedString: Look at it pour out there. Do you think it’ll clear up soon?

Text.SourceString: The fish aren’t biting today.//We might have to eat something else for dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: The fish aren’t biting today.//We might have to eat something else for dinner.

Text.SourceString: When it comes to preparing fish, there are a gazillion ways to do it. But let me tell you, nothing beats the sizzling goodness of grilling.//<portrait=normal>It really brings out the flavor.
Text.LocalizedString: When it comes to preparing fish, there are a gazillion ways to do it. But let me tell you, nothing beats the sizzling goodness of grilling.//<portrait=normal>It really brings out the flavor.

Text.SourceString: I wasn’t big on fishing before I moved here, but sometimes there’s not much else to do on the water besides catch a few trout.
Text.LocalizedString: I wasn’t big on fishing before I moved here, but sometimes there’s not much else to do on the water besides catch a few trout.

Text.SourceString: As much as I love the water, sometimes it’s nice to see some green too.
Text.LocalizedString: As much as I love the water, sometimes it’s nice to see some green too.

Text.SourceString: I'd lend you my metal detector, but, uh, I'm actually using it at the moment.
Text.LocalizedString: I'd lend you my metal detector, but, uh, I'm actually using it at the moment.

Text.SourceString: It's a blast sifting through the sand and discovering all sorts of hidden treasures.//It's like a special treat, especially when I find something cute that I can give to the kiddos.
Text.LocalizedString: It's a blast sifting through the sand and discovering all sorts of hidden treasures.//It's like a special treat, especially when I find something cute that I can give to the kiddos.

Text.SourceString: I brought some food along, but I have a feeling it might be a bit on the stale side.//<portrait=happy>Oh well, fingers crossed it's still somewhat edible.
Text.LocalizedString: I brought some food along, but I have a feeling it might be a bit on the stale side.//<portrait=happy>Oh well, fingers crossed it's still somewhat edible.

Text.SourceString: Volleyball isn't really my thing.//That ball is massive, and I gotta admit, it kind of scares me. I mean, imagine getting whacked by that thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Volleyball isn't really my thing.//That ball is massive, and I gotta admit, it kind of scares me. I mean, imagine getting whacked by that thing.

Text.SourceString: Ah, the wind is nice here.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the wind is nice here.

Text.SourceString: You gotta be careful when eating your lunch here...there's sand everywhere.
Text.LocalizedString: You gotta be careful when eating your lunch here...there's sand everywhere.

Text.SourceString: I'd rather bring my own coconuts. The beach shack has them, but gosh, they're pricey!//I mean, sure, they offer them cold, but I'd rather save a few bucks.
Text.LocalizedString: I'd rather bring my own coconuts. The beach shack has them, but gosh, they're pricey!//I mean, sure, they offer them cold, but I'd rather save a few bucks.

Text.SourceString: The lake is a nice change of pace from the beach and the ocean.
Text.LocalizedString: The lake is a nice change of pace from the beach and the ocean.

Text.SourceString: The sand here is certainly less gritty.
Text.LocalizedString: The sand here is certainly less gritty.

Text.SourceString: Caught up with <NpcName>Walter</> about digging up more of his family's lost treasures. He's bailed on the idea, worried the government will swoop in and nab it again, just like last time.
Text.LocalizedString: Caught up with <NpcName>Walter</> about digging up more of his family's lost treasures. He's bailed on the idea, worried the government will swoop in and nab it again, just like last time.

Text.SourceString: Honestly, I can't blame him. That gem must've cost a pretty penny.
Text.LocalizedString: Honestly, I can't blame him. That gem must've cost a pretty penny.

Text.SourceString: Pretty sure I saw a couple of birds flying around and carrying twigs this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: Pretty sure I saw a couple of birds flying around and carrying twigs this morning.

Text.SourceString: I think they were building a new nest.//<portrait=happy>I don’t usually get all warm and fuzzy, but that was really cute.
Text.LocalizedString: I think they were building a new nest.//<portrait=happy>I don’t usually get all warm and fuzzy, but that was really cute.

Text.SourceString: You know what? I like the way your mind works… It’s never a dull conversation with you.
Text.LocalizedString: You know what? I like the way your mind works… It’s never a dull conversation with you.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… What should we do this weekend?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… What should we do this weekend?

Text.SourceString: I like to keep my distance, not be too, er…chummy with the townies.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to keep my distance, not be too, er…chummy with the townies.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know. I guess some of them seem…nosy. Always asking a few too many questions.//That scares me for whatever reason.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know. I guess some of them seem…nosy. Always asking a few too many questions.//That scares me for whatever reason.
